00:18.468 --> 00:20.201
Got to read,
got to read, got to read,

00:20.236 --> 00:21.570
got to read, got to read,
got to read,

00:21.571 --> 00:22.871
got to read, got to read.

00:22.872 --> 00:24.807
Wow, I feel
the exact opposite way.

00:24.808 --> 00:26.007
Why are you saying that?

00:26.042 --> 00:27.810
Book report.
I wrote the due date

00:27.811 --> 00:29.678
on my arm so I would remember,
then every day since then,

00:29.679 --> 00:30.845
I've taken a shower
like an idiot.

00:30.880 --> 00:32.113
When's it due?
Tomorrow.

00:32.148 --> 00:33.514
Ah!
What page are you on?

00:33.550 --> 00:34.949
The cover.
(screaming)

00:34.984 --> 00:36.852
<i>Call of the Wild?</i>

00:36.853 --> 00:38.721
Is it about
an insane telemarketer?

00:38.722 --> 00:40.722
Or Gene in the bathroom?
I don't know yet.

00:40.757 --> 00:42.157
Hey, kids.

00:42.158 --> 00:43.826
Oh, Bob, this package
came for you earlier

00:43.827 --> 00:45.059
when you were putting
out that grease fire.

00:45.095 --> 00:46.729
See, that's why I hate school.

00:46.730 --> 00:48.296
We miss all the grease fires.

00:48.331 --> 00:49.765
Huh, I wasn't
expecting anything.

00:49.766 --> 00:51.200
Oh. Oh, yeah.

00:51.201 --> 00:53.167
(chuckles)
I-I remember ordering this.

00:53.203 --> 00:54.703
What the hell is that?

00:54.704 --> 00:56.271
I bought a remote
control version

00:56.272 --> 00:58.506
of the helicopter from
the movie <i> True Lies,</i>

00:58.541 --> 01:00.342
complete with a
clutching Arnold Schwarzenegger

01:00.343 --> 01:02.677
and dangling Jamie Lee Curtis.

01:02.712 --> 01:03.912
Hmm. Oh. Hmm.

01:03.913 --> 01:05.046
Huh.
What a beaut.

01:05.081 --> 01:06.882
Were you drunk shopping?
No.

01:06.883 --> 01:08.717
I call it "nighttime shopping,

01:08.718 --> 01:10.119
with wine."

01:10.120 --> 01:12.653
I bid on an auction
and, uh, yeah, helicopter.

01:12.689 --> 01:14.256
Mm-hmm.

01:14.257 --> 01:16.691
Fly, you bastard, fly!

01:16.726 --> 01:18.226
Hold on, Jamie Lee, I gotcha.

01:18.261 --> 01:20.596
I'll save you from Tia Carrera,
I think.

01:20.597 --> 01:21.864
I forget the scene.

01:21.865 --> 01:23.265
Hey, when does Mama get a turn?

01:23.266 --> 01:24.366
I want to save Jamie Lee.

01:24.367 --> 01:25.701
Lin, I just started.

01:25.702 --> 01:27.069
And I think
I'm really good at this.

01:27.070 --> 01:28.771
This could be,
like, my new thing.

01:28.772 --> 01:30.938
Dad, you don't want to be,
like, too cool.

01:32.308 --> 01:33.442
Hello, boots.

01:33.443 --> 01:34.876
Hanging like you do every day.

01:34.911 --> 01:36.311
Give it.
Geez, Lin.

01:36.312 --> 01:37.912
All right, let me just
bring it in for a landing.

01:39.883 --> 01:41.917
You can't pull off
that look, buddy.

01:41.918 --> 01:43.051
It's not you.

01:43.052 --> 01:45.386
Gentle, gentle, and...

01:45.422 --> 01:47.756
kiss the ground.

01:47.757 --> 01:49.091
(all groan) What the hell?

01:49.092 --> 01:51.058
How did that happen?
I landed it perfectly.

01:51.094 --> 01:53.161
(squeaking)

01:54.097 --> 01:55.963
(humming)

01:55.999 --> 01:58.099
T-T-Ti...

01:58.134 --> 01:59.902
Well, it had a good run. Of one.

01:59.903 --> 02:02.537
That thing is a piece of crap.
I'm getting my money back.

02:02.572 --> 02:04.071
T-Ti-Tina...

02:04.107 --> 02:05.174
Well, maybe it's okay. See?

02:05.175 --> 02:06.607
Oh, no, it's dead.

02:06.643 --> 02:09.043
Squi-Squi-Squirrel.
♪ I'm reading ♪

02:09.078 --> 02:11.513
♪ I'm reading ♪
BOB: Oh, Tina. Tina! Tina!

02:11.514 --> 02:13.015
(grunts) Ah. Thanks, Dad.

02:13.016 --> 02:15.017
I hate getting hit
on the head by boots.

02:15.018 --> 02:17.453
Uh, you're welcome, Tina.
Should we throw them back up?

02:17.454 --> 02:18.653
I kind of feel bad.

02:18.688 --> 02:20.221
They've been there for so long.

02:20.256 --> 02:22.690
(grunts) Look out, Tina!

02:24.494 --> 02:26.161
I just... froze.

02:26.162 --> 02:28.129
"And following
a skillful landing,

02:28.164 --> 02:29.998
"it broke into a million pieces.

02:29.999 --> 02:34.269
Please issue me a full refund
of $45 plus shipping."

02:34.270 --> 02:37.005
And send.
That thing was 45 bucks?

02:37.006 --> 02:38.373
Plus shipping.
Which was...

02:38.374 --> 02:40.174
also 45 bucks.
The hell?

02:40.210 --> 02:41.643
Ugh! What's wrong with me?

02:41.644 --> 02:43.312
I just watched everything
happen!

02:43.313 --> 02:46.147
The squirrel, the boots!
And I did nothing!

02:46.182 --> 02:48.116
(altering voice): Hey,
let's all be quiet so Tina can read.

02:48.117 --> 02:49.885
(normally): Who said that?
Face it.

02:49.886 --> 02:52.387
I'm not heroic like Arnold
Schwarzenegger in <i> True Lies!</i>

02:52.388 --> 02:54.723
I'm not even Tom
Arnold in <i> True Lies!</i>

02:54.724 --> 02:56.457
Or even in <i> Roseanne!</i>

02:56.493 --> 02:57.793
Come on, Gene.
Don't worry about it.

02:57.794 --> 02:59.361
That was just part
of being a dad.

02:59.362 --> 03:01.029
You'll have those
instincts someday.

03:01.030 --> 03:02.965
But what if I never
get those instincts?

03:02.966 --> 03:06.267
Maybe I'll just grow up to
be a very handsome coward!

03:06.302 --> 03:08.036
Dad, you saved Tina!

03:08.037 --> 03:10.806
You're a heroic man of action.
I can learn from you.

03:10.807 --> 03:13.141
Gene, I-I think you're blowing
this out of proportion.

03:13.142 --> 03:16.143
Though I did react with
a certain amount of grace

03:16.179 --> 03:18.013
under pressure.
What the hell?! (computer chimes)

03:18.014 --> 03:20.082
"Sorry, I don't give refunds
for crash landings"?!

03:20.083 --> 03:22.518
"Heliflopter"?!
All right, new plan.

03:22.519 --> 03:25.319
His number's on the Web site.
I'm calling this guy.

03:25.355 --> 03:27.356
He's doing it!
He's man-of-actioning.

03:27.357 --> 03:29.624
Which I call "mactioning."

03:29.659 --> 03:31.727
Hello? Is this Sheldon Felds?
This is Bob.

03:31.728 --> 03:33.562
GENE: That's it, Dad.
Give it to him.

03:33.563 --> 03:36.832
No, not Bob the crash-lander.
It kissed the ground, Sheldon.

03:36.833 --> 03:38.834
Kissed it. Maybe I should've
just bought it

03:38.835 --> 03:41.036
from The Hobby Hole.
A <i> real</i> store.

03:41.037 --> 03:42.403
Hobby Hole!

03:42.438 --> 03:43.772
Well, how about I just
come on down

03:43.773 --> 03:45.673
and demand my money back? Yeah,

03:45.708 --> 03:47.209
your address is
right on the package.

03:47.210 --> 03:48.710
So see you soon, Sheldon!

03:48.711 --> 03:51.547
Oh, and, also,
your handwriting is...

03:51.548 --> 03:54.215
not very good!
Nice one, Dad.

03:54.250 --> 03:56.618
Bob, don't you think maybe
you should just let this go?

03:56.619 --> 03:58.754
You know how you get.
You start saying

03:58.755 --> 04:00.389
"It's the principle" over and over.
It's the principle of it, Lin,

04:00.390 --> 04:01.890
the principle.
Yep, there it is.

04:01.891 --> 04:03.358
Wait, how did you know
I was gonna say that?

04:03.359 --> 04:05.561
I've never said that.
Right. Yeah. Right.

04:05.562 --> 04:07.662
It's the principle
of the thing, sir.

04:07.697 --> 04:08.663
It's the principle!

04:08.698 --> 04:10.031
Prin... ci... ple!

04:10.066 --> 04:11.733
Oh, well, it <i> is</i> the principle.

04:11.734 --> 04:13.901
And someone's got to stand
up for what's right!

04:13.937 --> 04:15.704
Things are pretty loud,
so I'm just gonna put

04:15.705 --> 04:17.906
my fingers in my ears.
Whoa, that's waxy!

04:17.906 --> 04:19.141
Am I shouting?!

04:19.142 --> 04:20.541
I'm going over there.
(sighs)

04:20.543 --> 04:22.077
I'm going, too!
No, you're not, Gene.

04:22.077 --> 04:23.078
It's a school night.

04:23.079 --> 04:24.913
This is my school now, Mom,

04:24.914 --> 04:26.582
the School of Hard Dads!

04:26.583 --> 04:28.817
So just call me Li'l Hard Dad!
Yeah!

04:28.818 --> 04:31.320
But, no, not that.
But, yes, he should come!

04:31.321 --> 04:33.322
If Gene wants to learn
to be a man of action,

04:33.323 --> 04:34.789
this is taking action!

04:34.824 --> 04:36.290
Okay.
Bye.

04:36.326 --> 04:38.160
Come on, Gene.
Let's go get our refund!

04:38.161 --> 04:39.661
Refund road trip!

04:39.662 --> 04:41.563
I forgot my keys!

04:41.564 --> 04:43.565
Yeah, he did!
Deal with it!

04:43.566 --> 04:45.900
Deal with it!
Yeah!

04:47.832 --> 04:51.635
Look at us, just a boy and his
dad, driving to get a refund.

04:51.636 --> 04:54.038
Ooh, I got chills just saying it.
Well, Gene, it's...

04:54.039 --> 04:55.806
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
Don't talk yet.

04:55.807 --> 04:58.542
I want to sample what you say
and play it over and over

04:58.543 --> 05:00.311
until I've got heroic instincts

05:00.312 --> 05:02.546
coming out of every orifice
of my body.

05:02.547 --> 05:05.382
Okay. Uh, it's not about being
a hero, Gene.

05:05.383 --> 05:07.150
It's about doing what's right.

05:07.185 --> 05:08.418
Papa, do preach!

05:08.453 --> 05:09.687
And it is our duty,

05:09.688 --> 05:11.121
to mankind, really,

05:11.122 --> 05:12.723
to fight for justice.

05:12.724 --> 05:14.892
Some people say you have
to learn to let things go.

05:14.893 --> 05:16.994
Well, you know what happens
when you let things go?

05:16.995 --> 05:18.662
What?! What happens?!

05:18.663 --> 05:20.497
You drop the thing
you're holding, Gene.

05:20.498 --> 05:22.499
And the thing I'm holding
in this situation

05:22.500 --> 05:25.169
is this bag of crap.
Nice! Listen to this.

05:25.170 --> 05:26.737
It's about doing what's right.

05:26.738 --> 05:29.006
(fart sound effect)
Wow, I sound important.

05:29.007 --> 05:31.441
Powerful.
Maybe take out the fart noise?

05:31.476 --> 05:33.510
No. It kind of makes you go,
like, "Huh, good point"

05:33.511 --> 05:35.411
<i>and also, "Good fart."</i>

05:36.848 --> 05:38.682
Mom, Mom, look what I drew.

05:38.683 --> 05:40.084
It's me when I'm grown up,

05:40.085 --> 05:41.752
eating tacos
with my monkey Sheila.

05:41.753 --> 05:43.254
Great, honey.
Yeah.

05:43.255 --> 05:45.189
How's the reading coming, Tina?
Oh, good.

05:45.190 --> 05:47.123
Really, really,
really good. Good.

05:47.158 --> 05:49.159
Okay, fine! It's going terrible!
I'm a slow reader!

05:49.160 --> 05:50.828
And then I get to a comma
and I'm like, "Oh, I guess

05:50.829 --> 05:52.696
"they want me to pause,
but for how long? How do I know

05:52.697 --> 05:54.831
when to stop pausing?!" I'm
never gonna finish this book!

05:54.866 --> 05:57.034
Ah! And I'm gonna have to stand
up there with the whole class

05:57.035 --> 05:59.002
staring at me and my armpits are gonna
sweat and my boobs are gonna sweat

05:59.037 --> 06:00.738
and all the sweat's gonna meet
in the middle

06:00.739 --> 06:02.239
and everyone's gonna know
I didn't read the book!

06:02.240 --> 06:04.508
(grunts) Thank you.
Tina, Tina, honey, listen.

06:04.509 --> 06:07.177
I'm gonna let you in
on a little secret, mm-kay?

06:07.178 --> 06:10.247
I didn't read any of the books
I did reports on in school. What?

06:10.248 --> 06:11.915
Oh, yeah,
I've never read the book.

06:11.916 --> 06:13.550
Louise! What?
You never read the book.

06:13.551 --> 06:15.452
Well, I mean, you should
read the book.

06:15.453 --> 06:18.321
It's-it's better to read the
book. We never read the book.

06:18.356 --> 06:20.423
How can you do a book report
if you haven't read the book?

06:20.458 --> 06:22.459
You just got to give 'em
a little show. Pizzazz 'em

06:22.460 --> 06:24.595
so they don't even notice
that you didn't you-know-what.

06:24.596 --> 06:26.262
Pizzazz, that's up my alley.

06:26.298 --> 06:28.465
I once did a presentation
on <i> Catcher in the Rye</i>

06:28.466 --> 06:30.801
with only a catcher's mask
and a loaf of rye bread.

06:30.802 --> 06:32.935
Now, that one I failed, 'cause
I didn't back-cover it.

06:32.971 --> 06:35.406
Back-cover it? Oh, my God,
Mom, Let me slap her again.

06:35.407 --> 06:37.574
No, it's okay.
Don't slap her again.

06:37.575 --> 06:40.577
Tina's learning. See, Tina, you
can't judge a book by its cover,

06:40.578 --> 06:43.747
but you <i> can</i> judge it by
its back cover. Mm-hmm.

06:43.748 --> 06:45.515
Uh-huh... Wait, I don't get it.

06:45.550 --> 06:46.884
All right, let me see.
Let me see here.

06:46.885 --> 06:49.018
Dog named Buck, stolen
from his home,

06:49.054 --> 06:50.454
forced to live as a sled dog

06:50.455 --> 06:52.289
in the cold,
unforgiving Klondike region.

06:52.290 --> 06:54.124
Oh, my gosh, I'm getting
so many ideas already!

06:54.125 --> 06:56.560
Musical numbers, choreography...
Musical numbers?

06:56.561 --> 06:58.462
Louise, you're on props
and costumes!

06:58.463 --> 07:00.064
I'm on lyrics and dance steps!

07:00.065 --> 07:01.998
Tina, go wash your face!
We got a show to do!

07:03.401 --> 07:05.469
S. Felds. This is it.

07:05.470 --> 07:07.471
Let's give him hell!
(over intercom): Hello?

07:07.472 --> 07:09.306
Sheldon? It's Bob.
Go away.

07:09.307 --> 07:10.941
Okay, bye.
No, Gene, come back.

07:10.942 --> 07:12.742
Right, right.
Li'l Hard Dad.

07:12.777 --> 07:15.279
We're not leaving, Sheldon.
Not until we get our money back

07:15.280 --> 07:17.114
for this defective helicopter!

07:17.115 --> 07:19.482
So do the right thing
and give us a refund.

07:19.517 --> 07:22.186
Well put. Yep.
You don't get it, do you, Bob?

07:22.187 --> 07:24.788
Sheldon Felds doesn't give
refunds to heliflopters

07:24.789 --> 07:26.923
who crash on their first flight.

07:26.958 --> 07:28.792
Stop calling me a heliflopter!

07:28.793 --> 07:30.960
We don't care how
fun it is to say!

07:30.995 --> 07:33.997
You see, I only sell those
novelty toys to make ends meet.

07:33.998 --> 07:37.967
My real passion is customizing
serious RC choppers.

07:38.002 --> 07:38.969
Well, what is that?

07:38.970 --> 07:40.104
This is my quad.

07:40.105 --> 07:41.338
I've made a few modifications

07:41.339 --> 07:43.607
for... poking purposes.

07:43.608 --> 07:45.309
(scoffs) That's dumb. Poke!

07:45.310 --> 07:46.776
Hey! Ah! Tickle, tickle.

07:46.811 --> 07:49.612
Tap, tap.
Missed me! Stop-stop that. Ah! Ah!

07:49.647 --> 07:51.382
Hey, there's something
on your shirt. What?

07:51.383 --> 07:53.149
Oop, got your nose! Quit it! Ah!

07:53.184 --> 07:55.786
So, shall I continue
to masterfully poke you,

07:55.787 --> 07:57.520
or do you want
to run along home?

07:57.555 --> 07:59.323
The latter!
Good day, sir!

07:59.324 --> 08:02.024
No, we're not going anywhere.
Okay then!

08:02.060 --> 08:03.326
Suit yourself, Bob!

08:03.361 --> 08:04.628
Wet Willy!
Ah!

08:04.629 --> 08:05.862
How is that wet?!

08:05.897 --> 08:07.463
LINDA: <i>Oh, she looks great.</i>

08:07.499 --> 08:09.632
You look great, hon.
Maybe the best she's ever looked.

08:09.667 --> 08:11.068
Give us a twirl.
See that tail?

08:11.069 --> 08:12.535
Real construction paper.

08:12.570 --> 08:13.670
Stunning.
Thank you.

08:13.671 --> 08:14.972
Wag it a little honey, will you?

08:14.973 --> 08:15.973
(grunting) Wag it, wag it.

08:15.974 --> 08:17.174
Shake it, shake it.

08:17.175 --> 08:18.841
That a girl.
All right,

08:18.877 --> 08:21.879
so let the <i> Call of the Wild</i>
book report rehearsal begin!

08:21.880 --> 08:23.547
Tina, here's the lyrics
for the opening number.

08:23.548 --> 08:25.214
Go ahead and sing it!
Go on, girl.

08:25.250 --> 08:27.084
Okay. Ring, ring.

08:27.085 --> 08:29.086
(weakly):
♪ Who's this calling on the phone? ♪

08:29.087 --> 08:31.721
♪ It's the Wild,
is anybody home? ♪

08:31.756 --> 08:34.424
Great lyrics, Mom. I know.
But you got to belt it, honey.

08:34.426 --> 08:37.027
Let your voice do the reading
that your eyes didn't do.

08:37.028 --> 08:40.230
That makes total sense. Uh-huh.
So can you do it with vibrato?

08:40.231 --> 08:43.100
Like this?
♪ Wild, wild! ♪

08:43.101 --> 08:45.535
(flat): ♪ Wild... ♪

08:45.570 --> 08:47.237
No, that's n... Okay.
You know what, try grabbing

08:47.238 --> 08:48.872
the skin on your throat
and moving it around

08:48.873 --> 08:50.541
while you sing like this.
♪ Na... ♪

08:50.542 --> 08:52.509
Like this? ♪ Uh... ♪ No.

08:52.510 --> 08:54.211
Let me try, let me try.
(vibrating sounds) (coughing)

08:54.212 --> 08:58.247
Gentle! Gentle!
Sorry. Sorry. Sorry.

08:58.283 --> 09:00.516
(groans) Maybe I should just
transfer to St. Mathews.

09:00.552 --> 09:02.953
What? You think those nuns
won't make you do book reports?

09:02.954 --> 09:05.122
People never stop making
you read books, Tina.

09:05.123 --> 09:08.725
It's a sick world! You got to learn
how to faux-dazzle it. Trust me.

09:08.726 --> 09:12.328
After tonight, you won't ever have to
read a book again. I love you, Mom.

09:12.363 --> 09:14.765
BOB: So, Gene,
I know it seems like we're hiding

09:14.766 --> 09:17.067
from Sheldon's helicopter
in a Dumpster...

09:17.068 --> 09:19.100
GENE: Very much so.
...but we're actually

09:19.103 --> 09:23.439
just r-regrouping. And now I
will calmly check outside...

09:24.476 --> 09:26.043
Oh, thank God. It's gone.

09:26.044 --> 09:28.045
I mean, regroup over.
Uh, we can get out now.

09:28.046 --> 09:30.547
We don't have to get out on
my account. I'm in my element.

09:30.548 --> 09:33.349
No, we are going to show
Sheldon that we're still here

09:33.384 --> 09:36.086
and we'll never give up!
Whoa. Whoa. What's that?

09:36.087 --> 09:38.688
Fish in the sky!
This was in Revelations!

09:38.723 --> 09:40.089
Kirk Cameron was right!

09:40.124 --> 09:42.358
You done hiding, Bob?!

09:42.393 --> 09:45.229
We're not hiding, Sheldon!
We were regrouping!

09:45.230 --> 09:46.863
And we still want our refund!

09:46.898 --> 09:49.098
Uh-huh. Swim, my pets. Swim!

09:49.133 --> 09:52.134
(chuckles) Your gently floating
fish don't scare me, Sheldon!

09:52.170 --> 09:55.005
They're actually kind of pretty!
It's a lot like snorkeling,

09:55.006 --> 09:58.108
which I've never done,
but I imagine I would love it!

09:58.109 --> 09:59.375
Ow. Ow.

09:59.410 --> 10:00.543
Dad!

10:00.578 --> 10:01.845
You're shooting BBs at me!

10:01.846 --> 10:03.514
Ow! That one hit me
in the nipple!

10:03.515 --> 10:06.716
That's his good nipple!
My good nipple is bleeding!

10:06.751 --> 10:10.119
Are we done here, Bob?!
You lose, I win! Also,

10:10.154 --> 10:12.155
I have a couple frozen
pizzas in the oven,

10:12.156 --> 10:13.623
so I'm ready to wrap this up.

10:13.658 --> 10:15.659
No! We're not done!
We're not?

10:15.660 --> 10:17.761
No! Two can play the game

10:17.762 --> 10:19.997
of having a helicopter
that shoots stuff, Gene!

10:19.998 --> 10:22.499
Two can play!
Wow, you sound really tough,

10:22.500 --> 10:23.934
even though you're holding
your nipples.

10:23.935 --> 10:26.036
This is war, Sheldon!

10:26.037 --> 10:27.904
MAN: <i>Welcome to The Hobby Hole.</i>

10:27.939 --> 10:29.505
I'm Terry, how can I help you?

10:29.541 --> 10:30.974
Hi, uh, weird question.

10:30.975 --> 10:33.176
Do you by any chance
have any RC helicopters

10:33.177 --> 10:34.977
capable of actual warfare?

10:35.013 --> 10:37.447
