anything like that, sir.

10:37.448 --> 10:39.149
(whispering): Follow me.

10:39.150 --> 10:42.952
Welcome to the world
of RC helicopter warfare.

10:42.987 --> 10:45.937
BOTH: Whoa.
I was hoping that would get a "whoa."

10:47.006 --> 10:50.008
We have to be pretty discreet
about our warfare showroom,

10:50.009 --> 10:51.843
as you can imagine,
but neat-o, huh?

10:51.844 --> 10:53.044
"Sky-sassin"?

10:53.045 --> 10:54.245
That sounds brutal.

10:54.246 --> 10:55.980
War is brutal.

10:55.981 --> 10:57.415
Of course,
we advise you absolutely...

10:57.416 --> 10:58.883
do not aim these at people.

10:58.884 --> 11:00.818
Unless you hate them.
Oh.

11:00.819 --> 11:03.854
Now, I need to know what kind of
element we're dealing with here.

11:03.889 --> 11:05.890
Well, it's this guy who sold
me a helicopter online,

11:05.891 --> 11:07.057
Sheldon Felds...

11:07.092 --> 11:08.358
Oh.
What?

11:08.394 --> 11:09.893
Oh, man.
What is it, Terry?

11:09.928 --> 11:11.362
Just stay away
from Sheldon Felds.

11:11.363 --> 11:12.397
Wait, you know him?

11:12.398 --> 11:13.531
He used to work here.

11:13.532 --> 11:14.898
He was fired.
Why?

11:14.933 --> 11:16.934
Let's just say Sheldon ate
a lot of food

11:16.935 --> 11:19.771
out of the fridge in the break
room that didn't belong to him

11:19.772 --> 11:21.406
and was clearly labeled.

11:21.407 --> 11:23.841
And when me and the rest
of the Hobby Hole guys decided

11:23.842 --> 11:26.643
to gently approach him about it,
he attacked us with helicopters.

11:26.678 --> 11:27.711
Hmm.
You see this?

11:27.746 --> 11:29.731
One of Sheldon's BBs
got lodged in there.

11:29.748 --> 11:31.815
And now I no longer feel
comfortable wearing shorts.

11:31.850 --> 11:33.217
No!
Trust me.

11:33.218 --> 11:34.851
You don't want to go
up against Sheldon.

11:34.887 --> 11:36.720
Well, I am going up
against Sheldon.

11:36.755 --> 11:38.222
He's on a whole other level.

11:38.223 --> 11:40.391
But I've got
rightness on my side.

11:40.392 --> 11:42.193
Oh, you've got rightness
on your side.

11:42.194 --> 11:44.261
Okay, then you're good.
Really? You think so?

11:44.296 --> 11:46.064
No, but I just realized...
why am I trying to stop you?

11:46.065 --> 11:47.131
I make commission on these.

11:47.132 --> 11:48.432
So let's get you all set up.

11:48.467 --> 11:50.435
Behold the Vanquisher.

11:50.436 --> 11:51.436
Whoa.

11:51.437 --> 11:52.870
Yeah, she's expensive.

11:52.871 --> 11:54.705
How expensive?
$300.

11:54.706 --> 11:55.873
That's not much.

11:55.874 --> 11:57.075
But with that missile range,

11:57.076 --> 11:58.241
(chuckles) she's worth it.

11:58.277 --> 11:59.477
$300?!

11:59.478 --> 12:00.711
Of money?

12:00.712 --> 12:01.913
It's not about the money, Gene,

12:01.914 --> 12:03.080
it's about the principle.

12:03.115 --> 12:04.315
Yeah, it's about the principle.

12:04.316 --> 12:05.348
Terry, please.

12:05.384 --> 12:06.750
Teach me how to fly it.

12:11.557 --> 12:13.958
Huh, it's actually pretty,
uh, intuitive.

12:13.959 --> 12:16.594
Yep, I probably don't need
to be holding you like this.

12:16.595 --> 12:17.795
No, it helped.

12:17.796 --> 12:19.430
You know, before I let you go...

12:19.431 --> 12:20.797
good luck out there, buddy.
Thanks.

12:20.833 --> 12:23.401
Okay, well, thanks
for coming in.

12:23.402 --> 12:24.619
LINDA: <i>There you go.</i>

12:24.636 --> 12:26.637
Mama's old tap shoes.
How do they feel?

12:26.638 --> 12:29.073
A little loose, but, um,
why am I wearing these?

12:29.074 --> 12:31.476
Because nothing's more
distracting than tap dancing.

12:31.477 --> 12:32.910
When your toes are tapping,

12:32.911 --> 12:34.312
they think the reading
must have happened.

12:34.313 --> 12:35.746
Now, follow me!

12:35.747 --> 12:37.248
And... a tap and a tap
and a tap-tap-tap.

12:37.249 --> 12:38.649
And a tap and a tap and a...

12:38.650 --> 12:40.084
And we're tapping
and we're spinning

12:40.085 --> 12:41.819
and we're spinning
and we're tapping.

12:41.820 --> 12:43.621
Hold on. So when...
 And a shimmy tap, a shimmy tap.

12:43.622 --> 12:45.022
Wait, hold on. We're
still spinning...

12:45.023 --> 12:46.791
A scooby tap, a scooby tap.
Scoo-Scooby tap.

12:46.792 --> 12:48.558
A wiggle tap, a jiggle tap.
Wait. What?

12:48.594 --> 12:50.461
And a shibba-dabba, shibba-dabba.
(panting)

12:50.462 --> 12:52.763
Scooba-dooba-doo, and no one's
even looking at you,

12:52.764 --> 12:55.366
what you didn't do,
and a-scabba-dooba-scabba-dooba,

12:55.367 --> 12:57.168
scabba-dooba-day.
Huh?

12:57.169 --> 12:59.971
And the book report's over,
and you got yourself an "A"!

12:59.972 --> 13:02.974
Ah, maybe B-minus, probably,
in my experience, you know.

13:02.975 --> 13:04.609
Hey. How's the tappin'?

13:04.610 --> 13:06.277
Great! She's like
a jazzy jackhammer!

13:06.278 --> 13:08.012
Watch out, floor!
Oh, yeah.

13:08.013 --> 13:09.814
So, I borrowed Teddy's
wheelbarrow,

13:09.815 --> 13:12.116
and I made it look like a
dogsled, and the only thing is,

13:12.117 --> 13:13.985
he said he wants
to be in your book report,

13:13.986 --> 13:16.187
so I told him I'd pull some
strings, get him a small part,

13:16.188 --> 13:17.855
and anyway, he's gonna meet you
at school tomorrow,

13:17.856 --> 13:19.290
you can work it out then, okay?

13:19.291 --> 13:21.325
Cool? Is that cool?
Very cool!

13:21.326 --> 13:23.794
You could tap with a wheelbarrow
tied around you, right, hon?

13:23.795 --> 13:25.362
Uh...

13:26.565 --> 13:27.999
Got to get up higher somehow,

13:28.000 --> 13:29.901
so I can see onto
his stupid balcony.

13:29.902 --> 13:31.335
Oh!

13:31.336 --> 13:33.237
I'll just climb up
on that roof! (laughs)

13:33.238 --> 13:35.039
Uh... sure, that seems
like a good idea...

13:35.040 --> 13:36.606
of something dangerous to do.

13:36.642 --> 13:38.675
Gene, you stay down there.
Yup, no problem.

13:38.710 --> 13:40.511
Ugh! You're back.

13:40.512 --> 13:42.513
Yeah, I'm back, and I'm armed

13:42.514 --> 13:44.948
with righteousness and this!

13:44.983 --> 13:46.517
The Vanquisher. I see.

13:46.518 --> 13:48.118
Yeah, go inside, Sheldon...

13:48.153 --> 13:49.386
to get your checkbook!

13:49.421 --> 13:50.821
Like her?

13:50.822 --> 13:52.423
I call her the Vanquisherer.

13:52.424 --> 13:54.025
I got it from The Hobby Hole.

13:54.026 --> 13:55.593
And then I added the extra "er"

13:55.594 --> 13:57.460
when I customized
the crap out of it.

13:57.496 --> 13:59.796
Vanquisherer?
That's hard to say.

13:59.831 --> 14:02.132
No, it's not. You just slow down
on the second "er."

14:02.167 --> 14:04.000
Vanquisher-rer?

14:04.036 --> 14:06.236
Look, the point is,
it vanquishes Vanquishers!

14:06.271 --> 14:08.172
Well, not if I vanquish it
first!

14:08.173 --> 14:09.906
Are you suggesting
an air battle?

14:09.942 --> 14:11.609
Perfect! Air battle!

14:11.610 --> 14:13.544
I'm gonna make
your precious helicopter look

14:13.545 --> 14:16.214
like the piece of crap
<i>True Lies</i> one you sold me!

14:16.215 --> 14:19.116
But first, can I shoot you
with a missile in your nipple?

14:19.117 --> 14:20.551
I was really excited about it.

14:20.552 --> 14:22.553
Let me think. No.
Air battle.

14:22.554 --> 14:24.754
All right, fine!
On three. One...

14:24.790 --> 14:27.692
Not to interrupt, but is this
the best way to solve this?

14:27.693 --> 14:29.092
Just asking. Yes! Yes.

14:29.127 --> 14:31.696
Two.
(whirring)

14:31.697 --> 14:33.798
Aah, aah, aah.
Three!

14:33.799 --> 14:35.365
I'm taking you down, Sheldon!
You're gonna regret

14:35.400 --> 14:38.435
the day you... Oh, my God,
you just hit me. That was quick.

14:38.470 --> 14:40.070
Time for the death blow!

14:40.105 --> 14:41.471
Not the death blow!

14:42.774 --> 14:44.407
Huh?
What? Terry?!

14:44.443 --> 14:45.810
Me and the Hobby Hole boys
thought

14:45.811 --> 14:47.411
you could use a little help.

14:47.412 --> 14:49.045
We did inventory
and then we came right over!

14:49.081 --> 14:50.547
Join the battle, brothers!

14:50.582 --> 14:52.550
My favorite things
were eating lunch

14:52.551 --> 14:54.118
and wearing shorts, Sheldon,

14:54.119 --> 14:55.586
and you took it all away!

14:55.587 --> 14:57.421
Now it's time to pay the price!

14:57.422 --> 14:58.789
I didn't eat your delicious

14:58.790 --> 15:00.591
roast beef
and cheddar sandwich, Terry!

15:00.592 --> 15:03.327
But your chopper's
gonna eat this!

15:03.328 --> 15:04.996
("Ride of the Valkyries" plays)

15:04.997 --> 15:07.330
Aah.

15:10.068 --> 15:11.268
Aah!

15:11.937 --> 15:13.937
Aah!

15:13.972 --> 15:16.140
RC net attack!

15:16.141 --> 15:18.508
Aah!
This one's for Jamie Lee!

15:22.981 --> 15:25.349
(yelling) (laughs, whoops)

15:25.350 --> 15:26.883
Whoa!<i> Whoa!</i>

15:26.918 --> 15:27.884
Oh! Oh, my.
Whoa!

15:27.919 --> 15:30.288
No!

15:30.289 --> 15:31.789
Dad, you're on a ledge!

15:31.790 --> 15:33.624
Yeah, but we won the air battle!

15:33.625 --> 15:36.293
Yeah! How's Sheldon's expression,
Gene? Is he sad?

15:36.328 --> 15:38.828
Is he crying?
No, he's eating something,

15:38.864 --> 15:41.499
and he's got a new helicopter,
and it's pointing at you.

15:41.500 --> 15:44.648
Ow! And there's
a dart in your butt.

15:44.649 --> 15:45.863
Father!

15:45.864 --> 15:48.229
Everything's fine, Gene.
I've got everything

15:48.230 --> 15:49.964
under control. Ow!
Gotcha!

15:49.965 --> 15:51.365
Are you sure?!
Yup.

15:51.366 --> 15:53.334
Ow! My butt!
Hoo!

15:53.335 --> 15:55.936
Uh, Bob, should we get you
a ladder or something?

15:55.971 --> 15:58.139
No, Terry!
Take down Sheldon!

15:58.140 --> 15:59.841
Hobby Hole Boys,
give him everything you got!

15:59.842 --> 16:01.274
(war cry)

16:01.310 --> 16:04.846
What? Wait, Dad!
What about the ladder?!

16:04.847 --> 16:06.814
That seems
like a pretty good idea.

16:06.815 --> 16:09.549
I mean, you're on a ledge, and
you've got a butt full of darts!

16:09.585 --> 16:13.588
Yes, but I also have a butt full of...
principles! Oh!

16:13.589 --> 16:15.323
So, yeah,
you guys defeat Sheldon,

16:15.324 --> 16:17.325
and I'll just work
on my upper-body strength,

16:17.326 --> 16:20.094
do some pull-ups, and I'll be
out of here in no time.

16:20.095 --> 16:22.896
I can't... do even one!

16:22.931 --> 16:24.765
You're incredible, Bob.

16:24.766 --> 16:27.200
Time for the... Sky-sassin.

16:27.236 --> 16:29.036
Luckily, I have
my Sky-sassin-assin!

16:29.037 --> 16:30.403
I'll go get it.

16:30.439 --> 16:31.939
Well, I'll wait for you.

16:31.940 --> 16:34.407
What is wrong
with you hobbyists?!

16:34.443 --> 16:38.179
♪ Up here in the Klondike,
it can get pretty cold ♪

16:38.180 --> 16:39.847
♪ The other dogs
are looking fierce ♪

16:39.848 --> 16:41.782
♪ So it's time to get bold ♪

16:41.783 --> 16:44.952
♪ But when life gets tough,
well, you just got to smile ♪

16:44.953 --> 16:46.721
♪ And better answer that phone ♪

16:46.722 --> 16:50.892
♪ 'Cause it's the call
of the wild! ♪

16:50.893 --> 16:52.226
(whoops) Yes!

16:52.227 --> 16:53.628
(whoops) That moved me.

16:53.629 --> 16:55.096
So, yeah, you just do that.

16:55.097 --> 16:56.898
And no one will even know
you didn't read it.

16:56.899 --> 16:58.466
Or I could just do it.

16:58.467 --> 17:00.368
Yeah, no, no, you should do it.
You should do it.

17:00.369 --> 17:01.868
It's your thing. You do it.
Right, right, right.

17:01.904 --> 17:05.573
Uh... Aah, aah! I can't!
I can't do it!

17:05.574 --> 17:07.040
Aah! Aah! Aah!
No, no, no, you'll be fine.

17:07.041 --> 17:08.442
Oh, yeah.
You just remember all the steps.

17:08.443 --> 17:09.877
You got those.
Memorize all the lyrics.

17:09.877 --> 17:11.244
Done. And don't mess it up.

17:11.246 --> 17:12.579
Boom.
Uh! Okay!

17:12.580 --> 17:13.881
I'm-I'm gonna go to bed.

17:13.882 --> 17:15.750
Uh. Everything's gonna be fine.

17:15.751 --> 17:17.251
Okay.
Uh. Good night!

17:17.252 --> 17:18.920
Yeah, get your beauty sleep.

17:18.921 --> 17:20.788
Oh, your wheelbarrow, hon.
You might want to... Aah!

17:20.789 --> 17:22.256
Ah, she's fine.
She's got this.

17:22.257 --> 17:23.758
We did good today,
Mom. We did good.

17:23.759 --> 17:25.126
We did.
Yeah.

17:25.127 --> 17:26.594
Hey, you want me to teach you

17:26.595 --> 17:28.596
how to get out of
a speeding ticket? Yes!

17:28.597 --> 17:30.130
Sky-sassin!

17:30.165 --> 17:31.899
Destroy him, Terry,
and I didn't catch

17:31.900 --> 17:34.301
all of your names,
but you guys destroy him, too!

17:34.336 --> 17:36.771
Oh, that's Vance, and that's Will.
Hi. Hey.

17:36.772 --> 17:39.073
Hey, Dad, remember this?

17:39.074 --> 17:41.909
BOB: Some people say you have
to learn to let things go.

17:41.910 --> 17:44.612
I know you don't agree with
them, but I'm starting to think

17:44.613 --> 17:46.614
maybe some people are right.

17:46.615 --> 17:48.783
Listen, here it is high-pitched
like a little girl.

17:48.784 --> 17:51.318
(in high-pitched voice): Some people
say you have to learn to let things go.

17:51.353 --> 17:53.486
Here it is super, super deep,
like a monster.

17:53.522 --> 17:55.322
(in deep, distorted voice):
You have to learn to let things go.

17:55.357 --> 17:56.791
Here it is with a beat under it.
(upbeat tune plays)

17:56.792 --> 17:59.159
You have to learn
to let things go.

17:59.194 --> 18:01.862
No matter how I play it back,
Keyboard Dad sounds

18:01.863 --> 18:04.497
a lot smarter than
Hanging from the Building Dad!

18:04.533 --> 18:05.832
I like the one with the beat.

18:05.867 --> 18:07.702
I came here today
'cause I thought

18:07.703 --> 18:10.972
I needed to learn
to be a heroic man of action.

18:10.973 --> 18:13.307
But look at you.
You're all nuts!

18:13.308 --> 18:15.643
Is anything worth all of this?
I mean, Terry,

18:15.644 --> 18:17.612
I'm sorry you can't wear shorts.

18:17.613 --> 18:20.514
I would be devastated myself,
but still!

18:20.515 --> 18:22.483
Also, just go to a doctor!

18:22.484 --> 18:24.685
Maybe sometimes
the more heroic thing is

18:24.686 --> 18:27.521
to just let it the freak go!

18:27.522 --> 18:31.058
Now, who's gonna be the bigger
man here, and just let it go?!

18:31.059 --> 18:34.694
I-I don't need a refund.
I'll give you your refund.

18:34.730 --> 18:36.530
No, I said it first.
I said it first!

18:36.531 --> 18:37.964
I'm the bigger man.
No, I am!

18:38.000 --> 18:40.200
Sheldon, I'm sorry we ganged up
on you about the food thing!

18:40.235 --> 18:42.003
I'm sorry I ganged up
on all your food!

18:42.004 --> 18:44.472
Well, I forgive you! Thank you.
Can I have my job back?

18:44.473 --> 18:45.873
No, you can't.
It's not up to me.

18:45.874 --> 18:47.308
Remember Roger? He's
in charge of it now.

18:47.309 --> 18:48.709
Can you believe it?

18:48.710 --> 18:50.911
Can someone just get
a ladder already?!

18:50.912 --> 18:54.882
BOB: You know, Gene,
in your own way, you kind of ended up

18:54.883 --> 18:56.984
saving the day today.
Oh, thank God you finally said it.

18:56.985 --> 18:59.153
The whole car ride,
I was, like, "Do I say it?

18:59.154 --> 19:01.522
No, he should be the one to
say it. I'm not gonna say it."

19:01.523 --> 19:03.858
Well, I'm saying it, so, thanks.

19:03.859 --> 19:06.093
Huh. Today started with me
wanting to learn from you,

19:06.094 --> 19:07.928
but then you learned from me.

19:07.929 --> 19:09.997
Does that make me
your dad now? No.

19:09.998 --> 19:12.198
Do you want to switch for
a while? I could take Mondays.

19:12.234 --> 19:13.901
Let's keep it like this for now.

19:13.902 --> 19:17.003
Well, you're still my hero, Dad.
You're mine, too, Gene.

19:17.039 --> 19:19.740
Now how about we go
inside and ice my butt?

19:19.741 --> 19:21.709
I wonder how many other dads
are saying that

19:21.710 --> 19:23.744
to their sons right now.
I bet a lot.

19:23.745 --> 19:25.513
JOCELYN: <i>And that's why</i>

19:25.514 --> 19:28.081
it truly was like
a tale of two cities.

19:28.116 --> 19:29.583
But I feel like maybe next time,

19:29.584 --> 19:31.252
focus on the tale
of just one city.

19:31.253 --> 19:33.854
And maybe that city is
like a yogurt shop

19:33.855 --> 19:35.423
where cool teens work.

19:35.424 --> 19:36.691
I want to work there.
Thank you.

19:36.692 --> 19:40.061
Okay, Jocelyn.
Tina, you're up.

19:40.062 --> 19:42.362
Hi. Hi. Hi, everyone. Uh.

19:42.397 --> 19:44.865
Good job, Jocelyn.
Thank you.

19:44.866 --> 19:48.035
(clears her throat)

19:48.036 --> 19:49.370
(sighs)

19:49.371 --> 19:50.771
(weakly): Ring, ring, ring.

19:50.772 --> 19:54.107
What did she just say?

19:54.142 --> 19:57.078
It's the...
call of the... wild?

19:57.079 --> 19:59.246
Aah! I can't take it!
I can't take it!

19:59.247 --> 20:01.081
(yelling)

20:01.116 --> 20:03.918
(kids gasp,
Tina continues yelling)

20:03.919 --> 20:05.952
(grunting)

20:07.489 --> 20:08.788
Wow. Tina.

20:08.824 --> 20:11.458
That was, uh...
Did you all see that?

20:11.493 --> 20:13.294
That was... Um, I...
I'm-I'm sorry.

20:13.295 --> 20:14.595
...amazing.
Oh.

20:14.596 --> 20:17.098
You just embodied
all the themes of the book.

20:17.099 --> 20:18.666
Huh.
The primitivism,

20:18.667 --> 20:20.300
Buck's return to his
savage nature. Yeah.

20:20.335 --> 20:22.068
The sweating. Great job.

20:22.104 --> 20:24.071
She was really good.
That was really good.

20:24.072 --> 20:26.272
Well, I definitely read the book,
so, thank you. LINDA: Huh.

20:26.308 --> 20:28.943
She changed some things,
but, uh, she still nailed it.

20:28.944 --> 20:31.779
She totally nailed it.
So... say it, Bob.

20:31.780 --> 20:33.347
No.
Say it.

20:33.348 --> 20:35.249
(sighs) You win best
parent of the week.

20:35.250 --> 20:36.650
Yes! Yes! Me!

20:36.651 --> 20:38.252
I thought I won best
parent of the week!

20:38.253 --> 20:39.854
